Package it.polimi.ingsw.Controller

Class MoveState

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.Controller.MoveState
All Implemented Interfaces:
State
public class MoveState
extends java.lang.Object
implements State
The MoveState is used every time a player has to move. It is usually built after the ActivationGodState and it contains the list of possible moves for each worker and four boolean variables which report whether the gods Apollo, Minotaur, Hera or Prometheus are active. the boolean variable points out if the action is the first one, because when Prometheus is active the move is the second action

  • Constructor Details

    • MoveState

      public MoveState​(java.util.ArrayList<Box> possibleMovesby0, java.util.ArrayList<Box> possibleMovesby1, boolean pushWorker, boolean swapWorker, boolean heraIsActive, Model model, boolean firstAction)
      Used to initialize the state. It receives the two lists of possible moves for the workers, the model and the four boolean variables which state if the gods are active
      Parameters:
      possibleMovesby0 - possible moves for the first worker
      possibleMovesby1 - possible moves for the second worker
      pushWorker - if Minotaur is active this is set to true, it allows workers to push others
      swapWorker - if Apollo is active this is set to true, allows worker swaps
      firstAction - if the Move is the first action in the turn (move or build) this flag is set to true
